							<p>
								<b>Some Academic tools I once developed</b>
								<br>

										<a href="makeCompileFeaturesByPtts.makefile">makeCompileFeaturesByPtts.makefile</a> - currently my favorite makefile. It is a makefile I recently wrote that orchestrates exection of numerous perl script files
										(here is <a href="makeCompileFeatures.makefile">an older version</a>).
										<br>
										<a href="http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~davidbur/CloneMe/">Clone Me!</a> little aid for cloning Legionella ORFs
										<br>
										<a href="http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~davidbur/OligoBarzel/">OligoBarzel</a>
										Split sequence into k-mer for
										oligo-templated polymerization
										<br>
										<a href="http://db.tt/l3tgQh">An Eclipse bundle</a> includes also Perl (+ EPIC + BioPerl?) + R (+StatET)
										<br>
										<br>
